Today workout at @limitlessfitnessmd 💪

A day like today’s workout is perfect for me because there wasn’t too many exercises that cause my abdominals to separate or too many exercises that would lead to a joint dislocation so I adjusted the stations I needed to, took certain options that were given to everyone at LF and used a little lighter weight than normal. 

I don’t really think of this as “modifications”.. I like to think of this as “customizations” 😏

Just because you alter or adjust the workout doesn’t mean you necessarily decreased the level of difficulty. You can improve an exercise and make it fit your needs best without making it “easy” or not a challenging movement at all. 

I’d say my modifications of 1:00m of Star Jacks and a Side Plank is just as difficult, if not more difficult than a Hurdle 1 Over and a Strap 1 Arm Push up. Most of my customizations are just a different movement that is just as hard BUT when there is an exercise or part of my body that is a complete no-go, I’m not afraid to do what’s best for me and my long term well-being and “take it easy” for that certain day or movement. 

Be smart, push hard on the things you can (on the days you can) and don’t be afraid to make some customizations if it’s going to benefit you in the long haul.

It’s all about sustainability and longevity when trying to continue your fitness journey while battling health problems and complications.

This ain’t for the weak so remember to be kind to yourself and don’t worry about what anyone else is doing or thinking.. it’s not their journey to understand. 

#ThisIsEDS #edsawareness #chronicpainfighter #hypermobilitysyndrome #diastasisrecti

It’s been one hell of a year. This is a list of the injuries, diagnosises or preexisting issues that resurfaced in the year 2022 because of my Connective Tissue Disorder. 

▪️Jan - Torn Hip Labrum (because of Hip Dysplasia)
▪️Feb - Torn Rotator Cuff
▪️March - Thoracic Outlet Syndrome + more nerve damage
▪️April - Subluxations (so docs added elbow braces and wrist braces to my list lol)
▪️May - Ribcage started to subluxate more frequently
▪️June - Tore the large ligament in my Abdominal Wall
▪️July - Torn ligament lead to Epigastric Hernia and Distatis Recti
▪️Aug - Dislocated my shoulder.. again 
▪️Sept - Fell down the stairs, dislocated my finger
▪️Oct - Abdominal Wall still messed up.. diagnosed with Costochondritis
▪️Nov - Doc concerned about my absent menstrual cycle, reproductive health, still no luck with pregnancy and risks of me carrying a baby anyway 
▪️Dec - Just trying my best as I balance a lot in my life, run a business of 300 clients plus manage my daily pain, symptoms, injuries, doctor appointments, medical debt and my own fitness journey 🦾🥹

THIS ⬆️ is EDS in one year. And my injuries and comradaries are actually SMALL scaled compared to a lot of other EDS warriors. 

Here’s the good news of 2022:
- Got tested for MS, that was negative 
- Got tested for a specific Spine disease, that was negative
- The hamstring they thought was torn actually ended up being a pinched nerve from my herniated disk
- Been managing my POTs symptoms and rambunctious Blood Pressure drops a lot better
- My Larynx and vocal cord issues magically disappeared
- Even if it’s on a smaller scale and in a more modified way, I still have the privilege to move my body every single day 🙏

#EDSawareness #edstagram #ehlersdanlossyndrome #connectivetissuedisorder #hipdysplasiaawareness #chronicpainwarrior #chronicillnessawareness #warriormindset #hypermobilitysyndrome #hypermobileehlersdanlossyndrome

I started 2022 with a broken body, a broken mind and starving for something more. 

In the beginning, I had so many questions, so many preconceived thoughts about religion and I had weak faith.. but I was desperate for something beyond what this world was giving me.

When I started seeking God, I found everything I was starving for AND MORE. 2022 was the year my life radically transformed. 

I joined a Freedom small group. 

I started listening to worship music and going to Christian concerts. 

I let go of my past. Resentment, anger and hurt from my biological father, my child hood and words of death that have been spoken over me by others.. wiped clean.

I lost my grandmother and not only leaned on God during the mourning process but really relied on Him for strength the 6 days my family and I spent in a Florida hospital waiting for her to wake up. 

I got baptized and embraced a new name, a new power.

I married a Godly man who loves and respects me.

Bad news from my doctors no longer affect me the way it use to because the peace and comfort in eternity really changes the way you see your temporary worldly struggles.

I continue to put my faith in God when it comes to my chronic illness journey and my infertility journey. His fingerprints are all over my life EVEN WHEN I didn’t believe in Him at all so I know He’s not gonna leave me now. 

I gave up drinking alcohol completely.

I became a God mother.

I learned to love other people in a WHOLE NEW way (the way Jesus did), to believe the best in others, to be slow to speak and get less offended.

I became more of an influence on my sister and introduced her to a newer, more contemporary way of knowing God.

I broke all my chains, stepped into abundant life and became new.

The more time I spend with God, the more love, grace and humility effortlessly flow out of me. No more chains. No more emptiness.

HE is where my strength is renewed, THAT is where I find unexplained peace in the hardest situations and toughest seasons. 

2022 was SO good.
God is SO good.
“And the good news is that I know He can do for you what He’s done for me. Let me tell you bout my Jesus…” 🙏

“As you celebrate the wonder of My birth in Bethlehem, celebrate also your rebirth into eternal life”✨

This day a year ago, Christmas Eve service a year ago was the first time I accepted God (back) into my heart.

Me.. the girl who was raised knowing God but slowly became a bitter atheist because of the battles this life has given her.

Something happened in November 2021 that opened the door of thinking about God again.. but the Christmas Eve service at Freedom church 2021 was me STEPPING INTO the doorway..

Did I become new and a born-again Christian overnight? No.
 
It took time. It took effort. It took mentors. It took ebbs and flows..

But here I am 1 year later, brand new. A Jesus follower who actually UNDERSTANDS what it means to have a relationship with God, who walks by faith and whose life has radically changed because of Him and His grace.

But what made me take those first steps back to God? The overwhelming presence of peace and emotional experience I had that night at Freedom Church on Christmas Eve 2021.

Even weeks after that, (I still wasn’t a full believer yet) but I kept showing up to Freedom on Sundays because of the unexplained peace I felt in that place.

Now I know that those emotional and moving experiences were the presence God. It was Him granting me unexplained peace and a place of refuge from the tough battles I was facing outside the church walls. It was God meeting me right where I was, as a broken, hurting non-believer.

I didn’t have to be perfect or “holy” for God to seek me, comfort me and send me unexplained peace.. and neither do you.

This gift of refuge is for everyone.. especially us broken ones.

Thank you @myfreedom.church for being the place I learned, laughed, cried and stepped fully into my new, abundant and eternal life in the year 2022 ✝️🙏💛

There is a big difference between adjusting the workout to your specific needs vs oversimplifying the workout so you don’t feel challenged at all. 

You CAN still train with purpose, have an effective workout and feel challenged even when “modifying” for an injury, for a chronic disorder (like me🤗) or just decreasing the intensity of an exercise because you aren’t able to do the most advanced option yet.

IF you are willing to leave your ego in the dust, give yourself grace on your modifications and absolutely DESTROY the exercises you don’t need a modification for, you can still make a workout just as challenging and just as beneficial!

Ways to change the modality/customize the workout to you:
▪️Decrease your weight 
▪️Drop the weight entirely and go body weight
▪️Slow your tempo
▪️Take yourself out of the unstable environment (ex: take your feet out of the straps)
▪️Incorporate Iso holds 
▪️Do a different variation of the movement 
▪️Do an exercise that works the same muscle group

Making customizations like that doesn’t make you weak, it makes you smart. INJURY OR NOT, if adjusting something allows you to work harder and still helps you improve strength, muscle and/or endurance.. don’t even question it! 

Customize as needed.. then take no survivors when you can 😈🤪

#modifiedworkouts #ehlersdanlossyndrome #chronicillnesswarrior #dowhatyoucan #diastasisrecti

“Every time we open our mouth to talk, we either advance the kingdom of life or we advance the kingdom of death”⚖️

You don’t need to be religious to make sense of that. 
You don’t need to believe in God to know that our words have power.
You also don’t need to believe in God to know that being nasty isn’t right, holding grudges isn’t right and not admitting when you were in the wrong isn’t right.

However, I will say that my faith journey has amplified these topics and has helped me so much when it comes to controlling what comes out of my mouth, forgiving others (even if they don’t deserve it) and just producing good things from a good heart. 

I’ve learned that if I want to truly live a fulfilling and peaceful life, I have to release anyone who has offended me. I have to CHOOSE to be life-giving even when it’s hard. And I have to bite my tongue when people are out here testing me 😮‍💨

A common dislike about Christianity is the “rules”. 

Rather than “rules”, I have found it’s more just a GAME PLAN of how YOU can live a better life.

Why were you given “rules” or guidelines as a child? For your own PROTECTION. It is the same exact concept with the “rules” God has given us about how we should treat one another. 

Harboring anger, holding onto resentment, gossiping and living your life “an eye for an eye” are all poisonous that really hurt YOU in the long run..

So from personal experience, me trying to live more Christ-like, letting go of my past and understanding the power of my tongue has brought nothing but life-giving, peaceful and positive things my way. 

IT IS HARD sometimes.. don’t get me wrong lol but it’s beneficial and I appreciate that protection.

I have really cut down the intensity of my workouts the past 8 months to recover and rebuild the multiple issues I have going on. But after another disappointing doctors appointment last week, I’m back to YOLO-ing it.

I am firm believer in modifying and being smart about injuries and pain when working out.. but when you have a chronic disorder that has ZERO solutions and is nothing like an injury that you can actually bounce back from, sometimes you have to pick and choose when to be smart and when to YOLO.

And quiet frankly, fitness is a huge part of my life and identity so if slowing down on my workouts DID award me with some sort of healing, restoration or solution, I WOULD continue to do it… but it doesn’t…

so I’d rather do what I love and come closer to my potential than not workout intensely AND STILL be in the same boat regardless. 

I will still customize the exercises that literally make my joints slip out of place or dislocate.. but I’m ready to get back to pushing through certain pains and challenges because taking a step back these past 8 months didn’t change a thing.

She ready 😈

The most important muscles that support and stabilize the spine and pelvis when lifting weight (or doing anything in life) are often the most weak and UNDER-ACTIVE muscle in the body. 

At limitless, we provide cues like “sew your rib cage to your belly button” in the middle of our weighted movements to guide our clients into proper alignment and to engage those small, deep core muscles, HOWEVER, you cannot expect proper recruitment of those muscles in the middle of a workout, if you are never training them and TEACHING them how to “fire”. These muscles are so small that doing the normal “core exercises” like Sit ups will NOT do the trick.

Diaphragmatic breathing and engaging your Tranverse Abdominis (along with your Pelvic Floor) is the first step to strengthening and teaching those small inner core muscles how to fire, stabilize the spine and pelvis AND breathe while lifting weights.

This is therapeutic for 1️⃣ post-partum women taking the first steps to healing their core 2️⃣ people that suffer from back pain due to under-active or weak core muscles and 3️⃣ ANYONE AND EVERYONE who does any type of Resistance Training because 9/10 people can not contract their Tranverse Abdominis without flexing their “6 pack” muscles. 

Give this 3-step exercise a try for 10-20 reps every single day! In the morning or even before your workout so you can “turn on” those small muscles that you have probably never turned on before! 

#transverseabdominis #postpartumfitness #braceyourcore #diaphramaticbreathing #coretraining

Early today I posted a Suicidal Awareness post on my insta story. I never come here for sympathy, I just come here to create awareness and send a message.

Suicidal thoughts is something I have struggled with since a young age because of battling a Chronic Illness. 

Getting no relief from pain, no relief from heightened times of suffering or any help from health providers can put you in really dark places sometimes. 

Chronic illness is weird.

Sometimes you feel like a bad ass warrior who’s got this..

And other times your entire body gives up on you with no explanation and you don’t look forward to the future because unlike everyone else’s temporary life hurdles.. your life hurdle is permanent and incurable.

I’ve been struggling through an EDS flare up for a week+ now. Lack of exercise, extreme fatigue and heightened symptoms/pain doesn’t help when trying to crawl out of the dark places my mind can go sometimes.

Chronic Illness gives you no hope.

But, thankfully, my faith journey has really helped during these dark times. Jesus and His word restores my hope. 

Choosing to be more eternity-minded really changes the way you see your worldly struggles. 

~ The more I decide to trust God with my struggles and suffering, the more unexplained relief I find ~
~ The more I focus on a higher calling and a lifestyle of giving, the more unexplained peace and blessings I receive ~
~ The more I CHOOSE to focus on gratitude despite battling an unfair and painful disease, the more strength to push through, unexplained energy and joy I have ~

Only Jesus can turn a mess.. into a message. And a test.. into a testimony.

So being a Christian doesn’t make my disease disappear.. it does, however, change my perspective and how I no longer allow fear and brokenness keep ahold of me. 

Being a Christian doesn’t change what I deal with.. it changes HOW I deal with it.

#ehlersdanlossyndrome #suicideawarness #godisincontrol #edsawareness #brokentopeace

MY PROTEIN BROWNIE RECIPE! 😋
I love Kodiak brand but I never follow their recipes (or any recipe lol) There is always a way to make a recipe even more macro friendly so skip the recipe on the back of the Kodiak Brownie box and try this ⬇️

Things you will need:
- 1 Box of Kodiak Brownie Mix
- Liquid eggs (different than egg whites)
- Cooking Oil (or Olive Oil)
- A mixing bowl
- A smaller, square brownie pan

Recipe:
1. Pour whole bag of Brownie mix in bowl
2. Add 30g of Oil
3. Add 46g of Liquid Eggs (equivalent to 3 eggs)
4. Add 1-2 scoops of Protein
5. Stir
6. Add water and stir
7. Repeat step 6 until you find the perfect brownie batter consistency
8. Pour mix into pan
9. Bake for 12-15 min at 350 degrees (I do 10-12 because I like them underdone)

Don’t forget to add some macro friendly ice cream 🤤

Your macros will change depending on the macros of your protein powder, the number of scoops you use AND the size/total number of brownies the batch made.

The macros for my brownies - 9 total brownies with 2 scoops of my protein brand - are:
8 carbs
3 fat
6.8 protein
Per brownie

#macrorecipes #trackingmacrosforbeginners #macroscoach #kodiakcakes @kodiakcakes

It doesn’t matter what you are going through. You can still have a great workout and see results in your fitness journey if you are willing to work hard, get creative and tolerate the bad/“off” days.

Today was a “we are just here to move our body” and a “we are just here to have fun” type of day (things I say to our clients who also battle injuries or health complications they have to modify for #IYKYK)

Rower✅

Can’t Chest Fly because it dislocates my shoulders so I Floor Pressed instead ✅

Can’t do a Band Waiter Hold (again, because banded tension pulls my shoulder out) so I did a light Barbell Waiter Hold ✅ (not heavy because then my wrists will dislocate lawl 🫠)

Star Jacks ✅ (which I can only do sometimes depending on what issues are flaring up at the moment but today was a good day because these felt good)

Hambridge Hold ✅

Can’t RDL because of my torn abdominal. I can’t do any bending over type of exercises especially with weight without my hernia popping out and putting my torn abdominal in more pain so I just did a KB Squat to upright Row.. why? Just for fun lol ✅

Can’t do a Shoulder Tap because I can barley do Push ups without being in abdominal pain so I just stuck to the Push up and eliminated the unilateral plank part of the movement ✅

Don’t focus on what you can’t do.. focus on what you CAN do. And when all else fails, just go in and have fun 🤷🏽‍♀️🦾

Crab Alfredo Macro Friendly Pizza

Ingredients:
- Reduced Fat Mozzarella (I use 50-60g)
- Crab Meat (I am cheap so I get Crab Claw meat)
- Cauliflower Alfredo Sauce (Wegmans)
- Pita Bread (Joseph’s has the best macros EVER)
- Optional Reduced Fat Mexican Cheese
- Old Bay

Directions:
Spread Alfredo sauce on the pita bread
Sprinkle Old Bay
Add crab meat (I do 3oz)
Then the cheese and the serving size of your choice (I do 15g Mexican 50g Mozz)
Pop in the air fryer for 7-10 min 🔥

Tips:
- If you aren’t weighing out peanut butter, cream cheese or any types of spreads or foods in jars the way I weighed out the Alfredo Sauce, you are doing a big disservice to yourself. If you zero out your scale after putting the jar on, every time you take sauce out of the jar, the scale continues to add up the total number of grams you have removed from the jar
- Joseph’s brand is the best brand for Wraps, Pitas and Flatbreads when tracking macros 
- Sometimes I will add shrimp to this recipe for a full out Seafood Alfredo pizza 😋

Tag me when you try it 😍

#macrofriendlyrecipes #macrofriendlymeals #lowcaloriepizza #iifym #macrocoach @josephspitabread

Between the normal day to day mundane stuff plus the heavy stuff life throws on top, it’s hard to remember to ~live~ rather than to ~just exist~

Thankful for our mini escape trip 💛
Thankful for him x200 👑

And just like that… all the sudden, all the “sacrifices” I made as I tracked my macros the 4 weeks leading up to our vacation were 👏 worth 👏 it 👏

“Sacrifices”… if that’s what you want to call them 🥱

❕Choosing to eat a protein brownie rather than eating Ben and Jerry’s 

❕Choosing to stick to the plan + eat the food that fuels my body best even on hard/emotional days where I just want to eat my feelings instead 

❕Saying “no” to chic fil a when I had nothing prepped and didn’t feel like cooking at 8pm 

❕Having the mentality of going to the event for the friendship.. not for the food 

In the grand scheme of things… I don’t look at any of these ⬆️ as “sacrifices”. I look at them as CHOICES. 

If you want to bridge the gap of where you are now and where you want to be, you have to start CHOOSING differently.

It’s not “sacrifices” or “punishments”, it’s about taking OWNERSHIP of your choices and how you treat your body! 

The choices that lead you to your healthiest, strongest and best self are typically the harder choices, yes. But what you choose is whats going to SHAPE your future, your path and your desired outcome.

This choices will cost you your time, energy and effort but the ~ return investment ~ is WORTH IT 💪

#healthierchoices #dothework #chooseyourhard

A year ago today, I made the personal choice to give up drinking alcohol. 

Even at my own wedding, my own rehearsal dinner, my own bridal shower, a year of holidays, birthdays, weddings, vacation and even one of my bestfriend’s bachelorette parties..

I still partied.
I still danced.
I still sang.
I still celebrated.
I still had a blast… actually THE BEST year of my life.. 
I just did it without alcohol.

I did it for myself, for my health, for my ability to think clearly and make decisions that align with who I truly want to be.
I did it for how I feel on a Sunday morning. I did it for the people in my life that are looking up to me.

I know I will probably drink alcohol at some point in my life again but I just wanted to prove to myself that I didn’t HAVE to just because I was at a social event or because everyone else was.

We live in a society that normalizes alcohol and revolves every gathering and every event around it. We live in a world that leans on alcohol as a de-stresser. I would NEVER judge or put people down for drinking… I’m just saying that if you feel like YOU don’t fit that narrative, that’s okay!

You don’t have to drink just because everyone else is. Don’t be afraid to step out of the ordinary and choose different if you are feeling tempted by different habits. You can still have fun, dance and celebrate along side loved ones without it. You can still de-stress and find other outlets when looking for a break. And ice cream and Shirley Temples are just as tasty 😋

Continuing a fitness journey feels almost impossible when battling a chronic illness journey. 

There’s a lot of mourning and a lot of disappointment in a fitness journey that has to be revolved around your health issues but I CHOOSE to try, to show up and control what I CAN control. 

I continue to adjust my mindset and my expectations because that’s the ONLY way I can continue to participate in a fitness journey. My body physically holds me back enough.. so I can’t allow my mind to hold me back too. 

2+ years in the making and I’m finally moving a goal over on the LF goal board because of that mindset shift 🤩🤘

Focus on what you CAN, not what you can’t 
 ~ chronic illness resilience ~

So excited to share that I passed my final exam last week and I am officially a PRE AND POSTNATAL SPECIALIST through the most credible Pre & Postnatal certification programs in the industry 🔥🤰🏼

Jord and I have always been ontop of keeping our pregnant and postpartum Limitless members safe, healthy and strong but a lot of exercise recommendations are conflicting due to lack of research and old wise tales passed down generation after generation. 

The certification I just completed through GGS is the most UPDATED and evidence based material to date and I have already been intergrading what I’ve learned into our LF member’s program and pregnancy adjustments. 

The female body is resilient and miraculous BUT there is a huge gap in women’s health ON TOP OF a culture full of unrealistic expectations for women.. especially their postpartum bodies. 

Closing the gap, delivering the most updated evidence, empowering and educating women through a healthy and realistic pregnancy/postpartum journey is something I am VERY passionate about.

When adversity strikes, you can either emerge stronger or you can emerge weaker. 

This is the part of Chronic Illness that is confusing for others to understand- people with chronic health issues have NO OTHER CHOICE but to fight, to be resilient, to emerge stronger.

The surgery I just got last week came with many positives as well as some negatives. They said it was more challenging than they expected but they did confirm that the “medical mystery” going on (and extreme pain that sent me to the ER 2 weeks ago 🤦🏽‍♀️) has to be due to EDS and my body’s inability to repair, heal and build tissue.

Part 1 of surgery was successful (creating an artificial opening to the organ that completely scarred itself shut ✅) but unfortunately, the negative findings part of the procedure lead to them not being able to complete Part 2 of the surgery… 

As we move onto the next step of this mystery process, Jord and I are just choosing to focus on the positive parts. I was cleared to workout (due to not having Part 2 done) so we are back in action today, taking things a little lighter and just happy to move.

THIS is the part that gets tricky to articulate and show when sharing my chronic illness journey. People assume that our physical appearance (or smile) must be related to how well our health is on the inside..

When in reality, most of the time I am DOWNPLAYING my symptoms and my health concerns and showing up with a smile anyway because I refuse to allow my health issues stop me from living the happy and fulfilling life that I deserve. I refuse to let “in pain” “medical mystery” “chronically ill” be my only identity.

I fall, I fail and I break.. often
But I rise, I heal and I overcome.. even more because I HAVE to 🦾

Todays workout was a perfect example of 🗣️ THERE IS NO SHAME IN MODIFYING YOUR WORKOUTS.

There were 2 exercises at every station today and I did something very advanced for 1 out of the 2 exercises then had to modify (NOT took the “less aggressive option” but completely CUSTOMIZED it with a completely different exercise because of my own health and injury history)

1. Pistol Squats (most advanced option)
~ BUT THEN ~ 2. A Kneeling Band Row (my own modification because I can’t do any type of weighted movements bent over)

1. DB Push Press (with an advanced female weight)
~ BUT THEN ~ 2. Bird Dogs (my own modification for the Scissor Kicks because I couldn’t do 1, 2 or 3 of the many options we gave to our Limitless members due to my abdominal tear)

1. Star Jacks (a “modification” for the Band Jacks to avoid a Rib slip.. but still an advanced exercise)
~ BUT THEN ~ 2. Pike Hold (modified for a Plank because again, can’t hold a Plank with my ab tear and Diastasis)

Trust me, I get it. I struggled for YEARS with the shame and guilt of modifying but it got to the point where I said “I’d rather workout and modify than not workout at all”. That small mindset shifted my entire perspective and my entire fitness journey. 

NOW, when I CAN do something without having to modify… I’m coming for blood. You best believe I’m starting that station early and putting my blood, sweat and tears into it…. 

~BUT THEN~ at the very next station, I may need to modify something to cater to my safety (these dislocating joints give me a run for my money lol) OR my pain… so I quickly shift into a grace-giving, no-expectation-having type of mindset so I can perform that exercise/modification to the best of MY abilities…. And then get back to destroying the  rest of the workout where I can.

It’s okay if your workout looks different than everyone else’s because you aren’t doing this for them.. you are doing this for YOU🫵🦾

In the past two months, I have had TWO different bartenders say to me “oh.. are you pregnant?” because I ordered a non-alcoholic drink after everyone else ordered an alcoholic drink..

As a woman who would LOVE to be pregnant right now but can’t due to health hurdles AND infertility issues, I don’t appreciate having to uncomfortably explain to a stranger that no, I am not pregnant.. 

But more importantly, I’m just here to remind you that being pregnant or having a past addiction are not the ONLY two reasons people choose to not drink alcohol. 

There are MANY reasons people choose to eliminate alcohol from their lives entirely OR just choose to not drink that day/at that specific event.
For some, it’s a proud choice.
For others, it’s a hard choice.

But either way, in a world that glamorizes alcohol, it’s a PERSONAL choice and an ACCEPTABLE choice so everyone should support it, welcome it and never question it.

#MocksNotCocks #alcoholfreeliving #normalizenotdrinking

Remember when I posted yesterday saying life is so good to me? And now here I am today, angry and questioning God again.

It’s easy to praise God and believe in His goodness during the good times.
And even easier to blame God and be angry at Him in the bad times.

It’s okay to be angry with God but don’t allow it to lead to lies like God not having your best interest or that He has left you high and dry to struggle alone. 

God does not CAUSE our pain and hardships. (That’s just the reality of being a human. That is the DIFFERENCE between our world and Heaven. If there was no contrast between Heaven and earth, the sound of a place that is pain-free, worry-free, peaceful and harmonious wouldn’t sound as tempting and as great if we were already living that way, am I right?) 

I’m not a fan of “just have faith!” when life throws you another challenge. I need more substance than that. So when I fall angry and confused again… I look for the proof and truth. 

The truth is that you have survived 100% of the hardships you have faced so far. 

And even when YOU thought you weren’t gonna make it out on the other side, God knew you were. He was in control all along. He never left you high and dry, He just knew how that hardship was going to grow you, what the adversity was going to teach you or why the “no” was actually just “I have something better, just wait”. 

THAT is the truth and PROOF I hold onto when feeling angry again. I remind myself of all the times I felt alone and questioned why “a God that loves me would allow this”… but the end results, the lessons learned or the path that the hardship lead me to IS THE PROOF that I really was safe (and victorious) all along.

Remind yourself that it’s just a bad day or a bad season… NOT a bad life or a bad God.

POV: you have a Connective Tissue Disease that continues to steal from you and forces you to give up more and more in your life (not just in your workouts)

You continue to watch your body fall apart more and more each year as your connective tissue decays and there’s nothing you can do about it.

You just have to “learn to deal with your new normal” when the newest injury or impairment surfaces because there is no cure.

You have to mourn the things you use to be capable of as well as mourn your future life that continues to get more and more foggy. 

… but you don’t quit.
You keep trying no matter how isolated, depressed or unlucky you feel at times. 
You continue to live by “no excuses” even when you have 101 excuses to give up.

Because wouldn’t it be a shame if you let the darkness win? 
Wouldn’t it be a shame if you allowed a disease to define YOUR ENTIRE life? 
Wouldn’t it be a shame if you allowed the weapon formed against you to ACTAULLY prosper?

My situation never gets easier, it actually gets harder as time goes on… but so does my strength and my faith in His plans, the people I’m meant to touch and the adversity I was designed to overcome. 

“That’s why you’ve been going through so much hell because hell is nervous about you reaching your destiny”.

I have to re-train my body how exercise (esp how to use heavy weight) EVERY TIME I have to rehab a new injury or recover after a surgery.

It’s like I’m right back at square one. Using lighter weight, taking no-impact options and learning what modifications my “new normal” needs.

Going back to the basics and slowly reintegrating back to your normal weight is what EVERYONE should do after an injury, health complication or surgery..

But most people don’t have a new injury or complication every 4 months like I do. 😂 Because of my disease and the nature of my connective tissue declining, I have to go back to “square one” every 4-6 months…

But the comeback gets sweeter every time 🤝

When we started this current training block at LF, I was still in a “recovery” phase from the multiple surgeries I’ve had this summer, using 60lbs less than my normal DB Front Squat weight.

Due to my patience, resilience and CONSISTENT rehab exercise OUTSIDE of my workouts, 4 months later I was able to make a comeback with this movement, using 70lb Dumbbells again 🤗

Hopefully you don’t have to take a step back and reintegrate as often as I do, but when life does hit you with a set back, I hope you recognize your resilience and celebrate your comeback.

Every. Single. Time.

I just completed 3 months of Pelvic Floor Physical Therapy. While it did not do anything for my Diastasis, hernia or external issues, it was very helpful minimizing my Pelvic Floor Dysfunction. 

My Pelvic Floor experienced a lot of trauma with the two back-to-back surgeries I had in July on my Cervix and Uterus. I’ll spare you the details but that season and THOSE SYMPTOMS were something I was not prepared for.

Here’s what applies to me, postpartum women and ANYONE experiencing pelvic pain, incontinence, prolapse or dysfunction..

❌ “Just do kegals” ain’t gonna cut it ❌

It is important to know how to isolate and contract the Pelvic Floor (aka kegals) but it’s even more important to address how you are going to APPLY it and teach your Pelvic Floor to automatically contract (and relax) during every activity in life.

The goal is take the breathing patterns and contractions you can do laying down in a “kegal” but apply it when standing up, moving, walking, lifting or exerting.. in AND outside of the gym. 

So yesterday I started with RDLs. Lots of activation, priming and drills beforehand but all that extra work will help build that automatic response of the Pelvic Floor and Core I need as I slowly integrate this exercise back into my routine 💪

Metabolic Training at Limitless 12 weeks pregnant.

Today was a partner workout and my partner @heather_n_schmitt is 31 weeks pregnant 🥳 so we had fun modifying (and destroying the workout) together.

When finding out they are pregnant, some women go into fear-mode, thinking they shouldn’t lift weights or do high intensity exercise. 

While other women STAY in athlete-mode, refusing to slow down and continue to push for max effort levels of training.

When really the answer is somewhere in between.

When you are pregnant, you aren’t fragile.. but you aren’t invincible either.

You CAN continue to lift weights and do high intensity training because ANYTHING can be scaled and modified for. But it doesn’t mean EVERYTHING needs to be scaled and modified for 💪
